{"action":"created","review":{"id":2405846059,"node_id":"PRR_kwDOAA2WCc6PZkwr","user":{"login":"rossbar","id":1268991,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjg5OTE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1268991?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar","html_url":"https://github.com/rossbar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rossbar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"> Do other folks have thoughts about how to set this up for numpy and not-numpy?

This remains an open question IMO. I definitely agree that this should continue to work for users who don't have numpy installed, but I can't think of a way to provide interfaces to the user to choose (or automatically select) which function is used that doesn't have downsides.

Given the first constraint (that at least some version of this function must continue working even when numpy is not available), we're talking about maintaining two separate implementations. Call the (improved) Python-only impl `def _random_k_out_graph_python` and the one here `def _random_k_out_graph_numpy`. Then there are a couple of things that could be done:

1. Automatically select which version is used based on whether numpy is available, i.e. something like:

```python
def random_k_out_graph(...):
    try:
        import numpy as np
        return _random_k_out_graph_numpy(...)
    except ImportError:
        return _random_k_out_graph_python(...)
```

The most obvious problem here is that *users are likely to get different results from the same inputs (including `seed`!) based on their environment*. Introducing an implicit[^1] dependency on the environment seems like a terrible idea from the perspective of reproducibility/code transparency.

2. Provide a switch for users:

```python
def random_k_out_graph(..., *, use="numpy"):
    if use == "numpy":
        return _random_k_out_graph_numpy(...)
    else:
        return _random_k_out_graph_python(...)
```

This avoids the problem from step 1 by being explicit, but introduces additional complexity/stuff to read in the docstring. And given this switch, it'd only be natural to wonder: are there other fnctions in networkx that behave like this? Do they all work this way (current answer: no). What if I want to use `"pytorch"`? Is this a backend? If not, why not? - how is this different from backends?

---

So - all that's to say: I don't really know what's best. Either way, that's a larger discussion and I don't want to let it block the nice improvements proposed here (thanks @TLouf !)

For this PR, I'd propose to actually include *both* the numpy implementation *and* the improvements to the Python implementation (perhaps as separate, private functions). Then we can hook both into the test suite and decouple from the API discussion.

[^1]: I say *implicit* here because numpy is very commonly installed even when the user doesn't explicitly do `pip install numpy` as it's a dependency for so many other things. This is opposed to backends, where the installation is explicit.","commit_id":"05ffe185045c00bf254eb80c9563d34dac574940","submitted_at":"2024-10-30T18:08:56Z","state":"commented","html_url":"https://github.com/networkx/networkx/pull/7702#pullrequestreview-2405846059","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/pulls/7702","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","_links":{"html":{"href":"https://github.com/networkx/networkx/pull/7702#pullrequestreview-2405846059"},"pull_request":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/pulls/7702"}}},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/pulls/7702","id":2153390273,"node_id":"PR_kwDOAA2WCc6AWiDB","html_url":"https://github.com/networkx/networkx/pull/7702","diff_url":"https://github.com/networkx/networkx/pull/7702.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/networkx/networkx/pull/7702.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/issues/7702","number":7702,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"perf: optimise `random_k_out_graph`","user":{"login":"TLouf","id":31036680,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxMDM2Njgw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/31036680?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf","html_url":"https://github.com/TLouf","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"I found this generator to be particularly slow, so I dug into it and made several optimizations. The main bottleneck I found was the re-computation of out-degrees at every single step. Updating their values at every step already allowed for a ~20x performance improvement for `nx.random_k_out_graph(1000, 100, 0.1)`. I then introduced numpy to optimize further to reach a ~60x improvement for this same set of parameters (from 2 minutes down to 2 seconds). There are more lines of code but not really more complexity, as most lines are for variable initialisations and updates.","created_at":"2024-10-30T09:41:02Z","updated_at":"2024-10-30T18:08:57Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"2fca021a72cdefcd0c86d3a13358f3349eaff6b2","assignee":null,"assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[{"id":121661134,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxMjE2NjExMzQ=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/labels/type:%20Enhancements","name":"type: Enhancements","color":"009800","default":false,"description":""}],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/pulls/7702/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/pulls/7702/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/issues/7702/comments","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/networkx/networkx/statuses/05ffe185045c00bf254eb80c9563d34dac574940","head":{"label":"TLouf:k_out_perf","ref":"k_out_perf","sha":"05ffe185045c00bf254eb80c9563d34dac574940","user":{"login":"TLouf","id":31036680,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxMDM2Njgw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/31036680?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/TLouf","htm